---
import GeneratorPage from '../components/generator/GeneratorPage.astro';
import { FREEFORM, PRESETS } from '../lib/styles';

const title = 'Free AI Image Generator — No Signup, Runs In Your Browser';
const description =
  'Generate AI images free, with no account and no queue. The model runs on your own GPU via WebGPU — your prompts never leave your device.';

const faqs = [
  { q: 'Is it really free and unlimited?', a: 'Yes. The model runs on your own GPU, so generating an image costs us nothing — there is no API bill to pass on to you, no credits, and no daily cap. The site is funded by ads, not by limiting you.' },
  { q: 'Do my prompts get sent anywhere?', a: 'No. After the one-time model download, generation happens entirely inside your browser tab. Open DevTools → Network and generate an image: zero requests fire. It even works offline once cached.' },
  { q: 'Why is the first load large?', a: 'You are downloading the actual neural network (~880 MB) — the same thing other sites keep on their servers. Your browser caches it, so it only happens once per device.' },
  { q: 'What hardware do I need?', a: 'A browser with WebGPU (Chrome, Edge, Brave, or Safari 18+) and a GPU with roughly 2 GB of memory. Most laptops from the last 5 years qualify. Each image takes about 2–6 seconds depending on your GPU.' },
  { q: 'Can I use the images commercially?', a: 'Yes. The model (SDXS-512-DreamShaper) is released under the OpenRAIL++ licence, which permits commercial use of outputs. Standard use restrictions apply — no illegal or harmful content.' },
  { q: 'Why are images 512×512?', a: 'That is the native resolution of a model small enough to run in a browser in one denoising step. It is the honest trade-off for local, private, unlimited generation.' },
];
---

<GeneratorPage
  preset={FREEFORM}
  title={title}
  h1="AI Image Generator"
  description={description}
  intro="Type a prompt, get an image in seconds. Free, no account, no queue — the AI runs on your own device, so your prompts never reach a server."
  faqs={faqs}
>
  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4">The generator that can't see your prompts</h2>
  <p class="text-[color:var(--color-text-mute)] leading-relaxed mb-6">
    Every popular AI image site works the same way: your prompt travels to their servers, waits in a queue
    behind everyone else, runs on their GPUs, and the result comes back — logged, rate-limited, and often
    behind a signup wall. Vexyn inverts that. The network downloads <em>to you</em>, once, and after that
    every image is produced by your own hardware. There is no server-side generation at all, which is why
    there is nothing to sign up for, no queue to wait in, and no counter ticking down.
  </p>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 mt-10">Made for a specific style?</h2>
  <p class="text-[color:var(--color-text-mute)] leading-relaxed mb-4">
    The open generator applies no styling — you get exactly what you describe. If you are making something
    specific, the dedicated pages pre-tune the prompt for that look:
  </p>
  <div class="not-prose grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-3 mb-6">
    {PRESETS.map((p) => (
      <a
        href={`/${p.slug}`}
        class="flex items-start gap-3 p-4 rounded-lg border border-[color:var(--color-border)] bg-[color:var(--color-surface)] hover:border-[color:var(--color-brand-500)] transition group"
      >
        <span class="text-2xl">{p.icon}</span>
        <span>
          <span class="block font-semibold group-hover:text-[color:var(--color-brand-400)] transition">{p.name}</span>
          <span class="block text-xs text-[color:var(--color-text-mute)] mt-0.5">{p.tagline}</span>
        </span>
      </a>
    ))}
  </div>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 mt-10">How it compares</h2>
  <p class="text-[color:var(--color-text-mute)] leading-relaxed mb-6">
    Cloud generators produce higher-resolution, more polished images — that is what a data-center GPU buys.
    What they cannot offer is this combination: zero cost at any volume, zero waiting at peak hours, and
    prompts that physically cannot be read, logged or used for training, because they never leave your
    machine. For drafts, iteration, references, assets and fun, local wins. When you need a 4K hero image,
    use a cloud tool — no hard feelings.
  </p>
</GeneratorPage>
